1. China adds 0! The central government continued to emphasize the orderly resumption of work and production

Figure 1

Summary of today's domestic: On March 18th, the new local cases were reported to be 0. Wuhan is finally 0! Wuhan new suspected, existing suspected also 0. A total of 34 newly confirmed cases imported from abroad were reported in China. The Central Politburo Standing Committee of the Communist Party of China meeting on March 18th called for a "full restoration" of normal production and living order in provinces with low-risk districts. Hubei Province will adopt the strategy of differentiation, division, classification, classification, conditional resumption of work. Chinese leaders have participated in more than 30 diplomatic exchanges since the outbreak of the disease, and Xi said the international community must foster a sense of community of shared future for mankind and help each other in the face of the disease.

World Health Organization group rejects 'China Virus' as more than $20,000 overseas

Figure 2

There were 20,602 new overseas cases, mainly in Italy, Germany, Spain, the United States, France and Iran. More than 5,000 people died overseas, another "tragic milestone. ".

The World Health Organization said on March 18 that it should avoid calling the new coronavirus a "Chinese virus, " which is not conducive to unity and cooperation in fighting the epidemic. Mikell Rui'an, director of the World Health Organization Health Emergency Program, said, "The 2009[ a ] H1N1 pandemic originated in North America and we don't call it 'North American flu' , so it's important that we use the same nomenclature when it comes to other viruses. "

Figure 3

Italy, Germany, Spain and the United States are all in the fast lane. France, by contrast, is holding up well, and that remains to be seen.

Figure 4

Inspired by the https://coronavirus.1point3acres.com/zh  website, the editor tinkered with the LOGARITHMIC knowledge he had given to his high school teacher, realizing that the logarithmic graph could give us a better idea of what was going on. We put the cumulative number of cases in several countries in logarithms here. Let's take a look (figure 4) . The first thing to notice is that the scale of the logarithm is an order of magnitude, and each bar represents an increase of an order of magnitude, which is the addition of a zero. Shushushuo has said before that the virus is not so much a bloodsucking flea as its vast reproductive capacity. A flea is not terrible, but after two or three months one million ten million fleas are. So that's the number one thing we've got to focus on. All reproductive processes are characterized by changes of an order of magnitude, that is, by an exponential function. The exponential function is expressed as a logarithmic graph that happens to be a straight line (the red line in a typical graph) and is therefore more intuitive. The secondary line (dotted line) shows not the area, but the slope. The larger the slope, the shorter the doubling time. We see that the current slope of China and South Korea is close to zero (horizontal) , the proliferation of the virus has been effectively controlled. When Italy overtook South Korea, it was in a clear position to overtake China. Europe outside Italy has overtaken China and is still on track to double in seven days. Although the United States started the latest, but in three days doubling the orbit, the last two days and even the trend of acceleration (slope even steeper than 2 days doubling line) , has surpassed the same period of South Korea and Italy, beyond China is almost certain. Sincerely hope that the United States states and the federal recent series of measures, in particular the detection of isolation system in place as soon as possible, as soon as possible.

3. Free new coronavirus testing is finally available in the United States

Figure 5

Nearly 3,000 new cases have been reported in the United States in a single day, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to nearly 10,000. The immediate reason is that large-scale testing is under way. On March 18th President Donald Trump signed into law the Family First Coronavirus Emergency Act, which will provide free screening for new pneumonia for all, including the uninsured, and ensure that patients and their families get paid leave, additional Medical Aid, food aid and unemployment benefits are also expected to cost more than $100 billion.

Donald Trump also said he was close to signing The Defense Production Act. The bill's entry into force will help accelerate and expand industrial productivity and support the military, energy, Homeland Security and other work needs. Defense Minister Espoo said the department would release 5 million N95-class face masks and other personal protective equipment from strategic reserve resources; prepare 2,000 medical suction devices; and deploy two medical ships to expand the capacity to fight the epidemic, each hospital ship is said to be able to hold 1,000 beds.

4. Germany faces "biggest challenge since World War II" , Italy 8.3% of health care workers infected

Figure 6

The European Central Bank held an extraordinary meeting on the evening of March 18 and decided to launch a 750 billion euro temporary asset purchase program, in response to the significant risks to the monetary policy transmission mechanism and to economic expectations in the euro area posed by the new coronavirus outbreak.

In a rare televised address on the evening of March 18, Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany, Merkl, said: "since the reunification of Germany, no, since the Second World War, our country has not faced such a challenge that calls for joint and United Action, " Merkl said in a rare televised address during his nearly 15-year term as prime minister. She had previously given a similar speech on New Year's Eve.

Chinese Premier Li Keqiang spoke by telephone on the evening of March 18 with European Commission President Gianluigi von Der Leyen. Von Der Leyen said that at present, the European side still urgently needs to purchase epidemic prevention materials, and hopes that China will continue to coordinate support. At the same time, the EU side is willing to provide necessary security and facilities for Chinese citizens in EU countries, including foreign students. China will facilitate the procurement of medical supplies by the European side through commercial channels. Later, von Der Leyen recorded a video speech, saying that China had not forgotten the help provided by the European Union when the epidemic broke out in China, and quickly donated more than 50 tons of anti-epidemic materials to the European Union.

Figure 7

According to China News Service, Italy's Minister of Emergency Civil Protection and spokesman for the new crown pneumonia epidemic, David Borrelli, said on March 18 that 2,629 medical workers in Italy had been diagnosed with the infection, accounting for 8.3 percent of the workforce, the medical workers are being treated in isolation. Hospitals across Italy urgently need to address the acute shortage of sanitary and protective equipment. But not all Italians are aware of the scale of the crisis. In Lombardy, at least 40 per cent of the population is still out and about, according to an analysis of mobile phone location data. The police issued a total of 170,000 fines last week, with more than 8,000 people being punished and individuals facing criminal penalties.

On March 18 local time, the second group of 13 Chinese anti-epidemic medical experts and 9 tons of medical supplies arrived in Milan, the goods include breathing machines, dual-channel infusion pumps, portable color ultrasound, laboratory testing reagents and commonly used drugs.

Another outbreak of concentrated infection in South Korea

Figure 8

New Cases in South Korea rebound to triple digits after 5 days. Of the 152 new cases, 109 were from Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province, 97 and 12 respectively. The rebound in new cases in Taegu is largely due to a mass infection of patients and doctors at a local sanatorium. As of 00:00 on the 19th, a total of 307,024 people in South Korea have been tested for the virus.

In addition, South Korea's overseas importation of cases has gradually increased. According to South Korean health statistics, March 13-17 border quarantine found a total of 16 confirmed cases. The Korean government is currently discussing additional measures to prevent asymptomatic infected travellers from entering the community at the time of entry.

6. Iran welcomes New Year amid epidemic

Figure 9

Iran is set for a Persian New Year holiday tomorrow, and the Tehran market is still said to be packed.

To help Iran fight the COVID-19 epidemic, the Chinese military sent emergency nucleic acid test kits, protective clothing and disposable medical surgical masks to Iranian forces on March 19.

[ special note: The above statistics, for the WHO official statistics before February 28, the data cut-off time is 17:00 China Standard Time; starting from February 28, the data from the "CAIJING" according to public statistics, the cut-off time is 9:00 China Standard Time. ]

7. Quick overview of the global epidemic:

U.S. gross domestic product will shrink by 1.5% in 2020 and may shrink by 14% in the second quarter, according to Morgan Mikell Ferroli, chief U.S. economist. It is one of the gloomiest forecasts yet of the impact of the new coronavirus outbreak on the US economy. This assumes, Ferroli said, that the Fed will continue to find "creative" ways to support the economy, with $1 trillion in fiscal support from the Donald Trump administration and congress.

As of March 17, more than 850 million children and young people worldwide, about half of the world's students, had been closed due to the new outbreak of pneumonia. According to the website of the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, 102 countries and regions have suspended classes across the board, while 11 others have suspended classes partially. This means that the number of students facing school closures has doubled in the short term and is expected to continue to grow.

The United States will offer free screening tests to everyone. China donates more than 50 tons of anti-epidemic materials to EU. In Lombardy, 40 per cent of residents are still free to move about.
